x4freetext: Well-type NaI(Tl) scintillation
counter. The 4pi beta proportional counter filled
with P-10 (90% of Ar and 10% of CH4).
BP
Sodium-fluoride targets were prepared by vacuum
evaporation of reagent grade NaF from a nickel
crucible to a thickness of =5 mg/cm2 on 1.8 mg/cm2
aluminum foil. A layer of shellac =0.1 mg/cm2 was
first sprayed over the backing foil to prevent Raking
of the salt during subsequent handling.  The
evaporation was carried out slowly in both cases to
prevent cracking of the evaporated layer. Punched
circles about 1.4 cm in diameter were weighed
individually and stacked between aluminum spacers of
1.8 mg/cm2 for NaF  for the excitation function runs.
Individual foil measurement. For
measurements of absolute cross sections at the
maximum deuteron energy, single foils were bombarded
in a Faraday cup.
By counting aluminum spacers foils, a correction
factor with a maximum value of 6% of the total 24Na
was obtained.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The errors are standard deviations in the
cross sections obtained from duplicate runs.
Consideration of errors involved in energy
determination, beam measurement, foil thickness, and
counter calibrations, together with the
reproducibility of runs under various conditions,
leads to an estimate of about 10% error in the
absolute cross sections for all reactions studied
except 75As(d,t)74As, which may be given in error by
twice as much, due to difficulty involved in the 74As
calibration.
page 1698.

x4freetext: Sodium-fluoride targets were prepared by vacuum
evaporation of reagent grade NaF from a nickel
crucible to a thickness of =5 mg/cm2 on 1.8 mg/cm2
aluminum foil. A layer of shellac =0.1 mg/cm2 was
first sprayed over the backing foil to prevent Raking
of the salt during subsequent handling.  The
evaporation was carried out slowly in both cases to
prevent cracking of the evaporated layer. Punched
circles about 1.4 cm in diameter were weighed
individually and stacked between aluminum spacers of
1.8 mg/cm2 for NaF  for the excitation function runs.
A stack of about 25 sodium-
fluoride foils separated by aluminum spacers was
bombarded for 5 min at 0.08 pA primarily for Na24,
with deuterons of maximum energy 15.4 MeV. The foils
were dissolved in 4M HCl. The individual foil
measurement was used for cross sections normalization.
By counting aluminum spacers foils, a correction
factor with a maximum value of 6% of the total 24Na
was obtained.

Punched circles about 1.4 cm in diameter were weighed

5 mg/cm2 for As for the excitation function runs.
A stack of 16 arsenic foils

cross sections normalization.
Fig. 3, page 1701.
